40|$|We {{present a}} formal {{operational}} semantics and its Coq mechanization for the C++ object model, featuring object construction and destruction, shared and repeated multiple inheritance, and virtual function call dispatch. These are key C++ language features for high-level system programming, in particular for predictable and reliable resource management. This paper {{is the first}} to present a formal <b>mechanized</b> <b>account</b> of the metatheory of construction and destruction in C++, and applications to popular programming techniques such as “resource acquisition is initialization. ” We also report on irregularities and apparent contradictions in the ISO C++ 03 and C++ 11 standards...|$|R

